<p><hr><p>

<h3>
  <a name="mobility-predict">Mobility prediction [2002-07]</a>
</h3>
<p>Leveraging Dartmouth's collection of wireless-network data, we
developed and evaluated methods to <b>predict</b> the next access point where
a Wi-Fi device is likely to associate, based on its past history.
There was a lot of prior work that provides nice theoretical results;
our papers were the first to evaluate all those algorithms with real
mobility data.  The results show that the more sophisticated
algorithms do not provide any substantial advantage, and that simple
predictors suffice.
<p>

<em>People:</em> Libo Song, Udayan Deshpande, Ravi Jain, Ulas Kozat, and Xiaoning He.<br>

<em>Funding:</em> DoCoMo Labs USA, Department of Justice (BJA) 
		  through <a href=http://www.ists.dartmouth.edu>ISTS</a>.
</p>

